pageContext.claim: “They did that yesterday in Minnesota -- the governor -- and I think he's paying a very big price for it. We had thousands -- we were going to have over 25,000 people. And you saw what went on there. It was ridiculous.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is annoyed at the state's limits on the number of people allowed at a single outdoor gathering due to covid-19. There is no evidence this is the case. This a hope expressed by a manager for an outdoor rally at Dodge Center’s McNeilus Steel. But then the Trump campaign shifted the venue to Rochester, Minn.
